data.title: Central Michigan University
data.text: Outstanding Chippewa quarterback who played from 1976-79 ... spent six seasons with the Dallas Cowboys, three with the Indianapolis Colts, and one with the Phoenix Cardinals of the National Football League ... was a third-round draft pick in 1980 of the Cowboys ... led Chippewas to MAC title in 1979 and was named the conference's "Offensive Player of the Year" along with earning first team honors ... completed 208-of-355 career passes for 3,088 yards and still stands seventh in total offense with 4,167 ... CMU was 19-2-1 during the two years he was a starter ... a product of Grand Rapids Northview High ... finished his NFL career with 9,436 passing yards and 49 TDs while completing 743-0f-1325 passes.
